While the primary role of a striker is to score goals, effective strikers also contribute significantly to defending and pressing. 

A striker who understands their role in defensive transitions and pressing schemes can disrupt the opposition, win the ball in dangerous areas, and help their team regain control of the game. 



The most famous recent example of a striker working hard out of posession can be found in the video.  Salah disposses Mbappe and turns a defensive situation into an offensive one.  

This section explores the defensive and pressing responsibilities a striker needs to master, broken down into key sub-sections.

